        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 12:42PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 1242 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles southeast of Gunnison, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pitkin, Parlin, Ohio, Waunita Hot Spgs, and White Pine.

This includes the following highways...
U.S. Highway 50 in Colorado between mile markers 167 and 181, and
near mile marker 196.
Colorado 114 between mile markers 2 and 7.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
